Proxmox Node Setup + Network Configuration

1.) Download Proxmox VE ISO + Create Installation Media
2.) Boot Node into Setup
3.) Configure the network on the MGMT until the web console is functional
    10.0.255.x/24, 10.0.255.254, VLAN 255
4.) Log into Web Console
5.) Create VLAN Interface for Manageemnt
    Name: VLAN 255
    Type: Linux VLAN
    IPv4: 10.0.255.x/24
    Gateway: 10.0.255.254
    Autostart: Enabled
    VLAN Raw Device: Physical NIC in Use
    VLAN Tag: 255
6.) Configure Physical NIC
    No IP, Gateway
    Autostart: Enabled
7.) Configure Linux Bridge
    Name: vmbr0
    Type: Linux Bridge
    No IP, Gateway
    Autostart: Enabled
    VLAN Aware: Enabled
    Bridge Ports: Physical NIC
    VLAN IDs: 2-4094 or Trunked VLANs
8.) Apply Configuration and Set Switchport to Trunked on Network Switch or Device
    
    
    
    
